ntwsClientSessionTc.name: ntwsClientSessionTc

revisions.description: v1.1.0: Introduced NtwsClientAccessMode to be used instead of NtwsAccessType from ntwsApTc module. (In 6.0, direct- and network-attached APs were unified.)
v1.0.2, MRT v1: Made changes in order to make MIB comply with corporate MIB conventions.

NtwsUserAccessType.name: NtwsUserAccessType
NtwsUserAccessType.description: Describes the access type by the user

NtwsClientSessionState.name: NtwsClientSessionState
NtwsClientSessionState.description: Enumeration of the client session states. Value 'associated(1)' applies only to wireless sessions. Value 'wired(8)' applies only to wired sessions.

NtwsClientDot1xState.name: NtwsClientDot1xState
NtwsClientDot1xState.description: Enumeration of the dot1x states for a client.

NtwsClientAuthenProtocolType.name: NtwsClientAuthenProtocolType
NtwsClientAuthenProtocolType.description: Enumeration of the dot1x client authentication protocol types.

NtwsClientAccessMode.name: NtwsClientAccessMode
NtwsClientAccessMode.description: Describes the access mode (type) used by client. Value 'ap(2)' indicates a client that is attached to the switch via an access point. Value 'wired(3)' indicates a client that is attached to the switch via the wired network (no access point is involved).
